[30.482, "o", "\r\n\u001b[38;2;142;68;207m\u001b[1m  ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ novaflow.ai SYNTHESIS ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ‚ĒĀ\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    # BRCA1 ‚ÄĒ Expert Analysis\r\n    **Biological function.** BRCA1 is the central scaffolding E3 ubiquitin ligase of the homologous recombination (HR) repair pathway. At double-strand breaks, it forms three mutually exclusive complexes ‚ÄĒ BRCA1-A (with Abraxas/RAP80, restricting end resection), BRCA1-B (with FANCJ/BRIP1, replication fork support), and BRCA1-C (with CtIP, licensing 5‚Ä≤‚Üí3‚Ä≤ end resection and committing the break to HR over NHEJ). The BRCT tandem domain (residues ~1646‚Äď1859) reads pSer-x-x-Phe motifs on phosphorylated partners; the N-terminal RING domain heterodimerizes with BARD1 to confer ubiquitin ligase activity. Loss of either domain abolishes HR and forces error-prone repair by NHEJ or microhomology-mediated end joining (MMEJ/TMEJ via POLQ), driving the genomic instability signature (COSMIC SBS3) seen in BRCA1-null tumors. The 47 transcripts / 33 protein-coding isoforms reflect biologically meaningful splicing ‚ÄĒ BRCA1-őĒ11q in particular retains partial PARP inhibitor resistance "]
[0.000, "o", "and is a documented mechanism of acquired resistance in the clinic.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    **Key variants.** The pathogenic landscape is dominated by truncating variants distributed across the gene, with two Ashkenazi founder alleles (c.68_69delAG / 185delAG and c.5266dupC / 5382insC) accounting for the majority of carriers in that population. Missense variants are pathogenic almost exclusively when they hit the RING (e.g., C61G) or BRCT (e.g., M1775R, A1708E) domains; missense calls outside these regions should default to VUS pending functional data. Large genomic rearrangements account for ~10% of pathogenic alleles and are missed by short-read panels that don't include MLPA or CNV calling ‚ÄĒ this is a recurring source of false-negative clinical reports. The 44.1% GC content and 125 kb genomic footprint are unremarkable; the clinically relevant complexity is exonic, not structural.\r\n    **Disease associations.** Germline loss-of-function confers ~65‚Äď72% lifetime breast cancer risk and ~40‚Äď45% ovarian cancer risk, with elevated risk for pancreatic, prostate (aggressive subtypes), and cont"]
[0.000, "o", "ralateral breast disease. BRCA1-driven breast cancers are disproportionately triple-negative, basal-like, and early-onset (median dx ~40s). Somatic BRCA1 loss plus promoter hypermethylation defines a parallel \"BRCAness\" phenotype in ~10‚Äď20% of sporadic high-grade serous ovarian carcinomas ‚ÄĒ these tumors are clinically actionable even without a germline finding. The synthetic lethality with PARP1 is the basis for olaparib, rucaparib, niraparib, and talazoparib approvals; HRD score (genomic scar assays ‚ÄĒ LOH, TAI, LST) is the validated companion biomarker when sequencing alone is ambiguous.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    **Experimental recommendations.** For variant interpretation, run saturation genome editing (SGE) across the RING and BRCT domains ‚ÄĒ Findlay et al.'s 2018 SGE map remains the gold standard reference and should be the first lookup for any BRCT missense VUS. For functional validation, use HR reporter assays (DR-GFP) in BRCA1-null backgrounds (HCC1937, UWB1.289) with isogenic add-back, paired with RAD51 foci formation after ionizing radiation. For therapeutic studies, profile PARP inhibitor sensitivity alongside resistance mechanisms: 53BP1/Shieldin pathway loss, BRCA1 reversion mutations, and őĒ11q isoform expression ‚ÄĒ all three are documented clinical resistance routes and should be reported together, not in isolation. For population studies, ensure the assay covers large rearrangements (MLPA or long-read sequencing); panel-only designs systematically under-ascertain carriers.\r\n    **Clinical translation.** Any patient-facing report should distinguish germline from somatic findings, flag VUS explicitly"]
[0.000, "o", " against the ENIGMA/ClinVar expert-panel classification (not aggregate ClinVar), and recommend cascade testing for first-degree relatives on confirmed pathogenic calls. HRD testing is appropriate when BRCA1/2 sequencing is negative but the clinical and histologic phenotype suggests HR deficiency.\r\n"]
